<!-- 05 BRAND NOTES -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">05 · Brand-specific cleaning notes</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What's distinct on each brand.</h2>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Bosch / Thermador.</strong> PowerWash zone (lower right) gives concentrated wash for heavily soiled cookware. Lower spray arm pops up; upper pulls down. Bosch 800-series CrystalDry and Thermador StarSpeed wash systems share parts platform.</li>
      <li><strong>Miele.</strong> Three-tier spray system (lower, middle, upper). AutoOpen Drying releases the door at end of cycle. Miele wash pumps have the longest service life of any major brand (year 12 to 15 typical) but parts cost more.</li>
      <li><strong>KitchenAid / Whirlpool / Maytag.</strong> FreeFlex middle rack and ProWash sensor systems. Lower spray arm typically pops off without tools.</li>
      <li><strong>Samsung.</strong> StormWash zone for cookware. WaterWall (on premium models) replaces conventional spray arm with a moving water-curtain bar. WaterWall service is brand-specific.</li>
      <li><strong>LG.</strong> QuadWash four spray arms. TrueSteam steam injection on premium models. Direct Drive wash motor (different architecture from belt-driven competitors).</li>
      <li><strong>GE Profile / Café.</strong> Dedicated bottle wash jets on premium models. Three-arm wash system.</li>
      <li><strong>Cove.</strong> Sub-Zero Group premium line. Heat-dry plus auto-open dry. Premium parts pipeline through Sub-Zero authorized network.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 06 REPAIR VS REPLACE -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">06 · Repair vs replace</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">When the math tilts toward replacement.</h2>

    <p>Under 8 years old, repair almost always. Spray arm clean, dispenser replacement, even wash pump are all under-$800 fixes that buy years more service.</p>

    <p>8 to 12 years on mid-tier units (under $1,200 original), repair-vs-replace turns case-by-case. A wash pump on a $700 dishwasher is a real conversation; replacement runs $700 to $1,200 plus install, repair $480 to $820. We do the math out loud.</p>

    <p>Premium and luxury units (Bosch 800-series, Miele, Thermador, Cove, KitchenAid premium) almost always repair through year 12 to 15. Replacement runs $1,800 to $3,500+ before installation, and the chassis outlasts the components. Wash pump on a 10-year-old Miele equals straightforward repair.</p>
  </div>
</section>

